The paper focuses on human pose tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves incorporating single-person pose tracking and visual object tracking, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) subfields. The use of a Siamese Graph Convolution Network for human pose matching involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subfields.
